    "body": "From [here](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/5490437942967638bcc6198035315f6811febaa8/p2p/server.go#L91):\r\n\r\n```\r\n\t// Trusted nodes are used as pre-configured connections which are always\r\n\t// allowed to connect, even above the peer limit.\r\n\tTrustedNodes []*discover.Node\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere are various questions about Trusted Nodes on Stack Exchange ([example](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/6821/how-does-ethereum-client-select-which-peers-to-synchronise-with/6922#6922), another [example](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/2478/what-is-the-difference-between-a-static-node-and-a-trusted-node)).",
